159
00:16:26,157 --> 00:16:28,831
How long do you think
it will take to find the killer?

160
00:16:28,993 --> 00:16:32,702
Right now the killer is being
surrounded by a web of deduction...

161
00:16:32,864 --> 00:16:36,038
forensic science
and the latest in technology...

162
00:16:36,200 --> 00:16:39,511
such as two-way radios
and e-mail.

163
00:16:40,104 --> 00:16:44,610
Assign a man to be his driver who can
report on his whereabouts at all times.

164
00:16:44,776 --> 00:16:46,778
What kind of man?

165
00:16:46,944 --> 00:16:50,949
A man who follows orders
and doesn't ask questions.

166
00:16:51,482 --> 00:16:54,759
Inspector, do you know if the killer
was a man or a woman?

167
00:16:54,919 --> 00:16:58,731
Well, of course I know that.
What else is there? A kitten?

168
00:16:58,890 --> 00:17:00,801
Excuse me,
do you think it's possible...

169
00:17:00,958 --> 00:17:03,131
that the killer could be
watching you now?

170
00:17:03,294 --> 00:17:06,002
Well, if I was a killer,
I would certainly be watching...

171
00:17:06,164 --> 00:17:08,371
and possibly taping
for later playback...

172
00:17:08,533 --> 00:17:12,606
because, you know, it's a big deal
to be talked about on TV.

173
00:17:13,137 --> 00:17:14,946
But I have a message for the killer.

174
00:17:15,707 --> 00:17:17,880
There is no place you can hide.

175
00:17:18,042 --> 00:17:20,989
There is no place
you cannot be seen.

176
00:17:21,145 --> 00:17:24,149
Killer, I will find you...

177
00:17:24,315 --> 00:17:26,659
because I am
a servant of the nation.

178
00:17:26,818 --> 00:17:29,196
Because justice is justice...

179
00:17:29,354 --> 00:17:33,496
and because France is France.

180
00:17:47,305 --> 00:17:50,252
- Bonjour, Nicole.
- Good morning, inspector.

181
00:17:50,408 --> 00:17:52,319
Welcome to your new office.

182
00:17:52,477 --> 00:17:55,287
You should probably start
by going through these files.

183
00:17:57,382 --> 00:18:01,660
