- Well, of course I'm all right.

190
00:18:38,623 --> 00:18:40,625
And what is that?

191
00:18:40,792 --> 00:18:43,363
- What?
- Nothing.

192
00:18:44,128 --> 00:18:48,668
You should probably start
by looking at these files. You have to...

193
00:18:58,643 --> 00:19:01,123
My leg, it crushed my leg!

194
00:19:10,755 --> 00:19:13,463
Being an inspector,
you'll need some new clothes.

195
00:19:13,724 --> 00:19:16,398
I can take your measurements
and have something sent over.

196
00:19:16,561 --> 00:19:18,268
- Of course.
- Please remove your jacket.

197
00:19:18,429 --> 00:19:19,965
Yes.

198
00:19:20,865 --> 00:19:24,438
- Do you live by yourself, inspector?
- Yes, I do.

199
00:19:25,336 --> 00:19:26,576
Do you get lonely?

200
00:19:26,737 --> 00:19:28,978
No, not really.
Not since the Internet.

201
00:19:29,140 --> 00:19:32,144
Well, that takes care of that.
And welcome to Paris.

202
00:19:32,310 --> 00:19:34,051
Thank you.

203
00:19:34,545 --> 00:19:36,388
Good morning, monsieur.

204
00:19:36,581 --> 00:19:38,288
And you are?

205
00:19:38,449 --> 00:19:40,929
Gilbert Ponton.
Detective, second class.

206
00:19:41,085 --> 00:19:42,792
I've been assigned to work with you.

207
00:19:42,954 --> 00:19:45,195
What qualifications do you have
for police work?

208
00:19:45,356 --> 00:19:48,030
My family's done police work
in Paris for nine generations.

209
00:19:48,192 --> 00:19:51,730
- And before that?
- We were policemen for 200 years.

210
00:19:51,896 --> 00:19:54,502
- And before that?
- Immigrants from countries in Europe.

211
00:19:54,665 --> 00:19:56,838
- All involved in police work.
- And before that?

212
00:19:57,001 --> 00:19:58,605
Farmers.

213
00:19:59,737 --> 00:20:03,947
So you are a little lamb who has
come to Clouseau for to learn.

214
00:20:04,475 --> 00:20:08,981
Gilbert Ponton, I vow to teach you
everything I know about police work.

215
00:20:09,146 --> 00:20:10,420
And together...

216
00:20:10,581 --> 00:20:13,619
we are going to catch a killer.

217
00:20:16,721 --> 00:20:17,961
There.

218
00:20:18,122 --> 00:20:21,899
The Chinese VIP box,
right on the edge of the kill zone.

219
00:20:22,059 --> 00:20:26,201
The poison was Chinese.
Was Gluant ever in China?

220
00:20:26,364 --> 00:20:28,935
Three years ago, he took a group
of French stars there...

221
00:20:29,100 --> 00:20:30,579
for some exhibition games.

222
00:20:31,135 --> 00:20:33,479
Gluant was in China.

223
00:20:33,638 --> 00:20:35,549
The poison is from China.

224
00:20:35,706 --> 00:20:37,777
The Chinese are from China.

225
00:20:38,109 --> 00:20:43,115
It may be too early to say for certain,
but I think our killer is Chinese.

226
00:20:43,281 --> 00:20:45,591
Corbeille, I want you
on the next flight to Beijing.

227
00:20:45,750 --> 00:20:48,629
Find out what Gluant did there,
who he saw, where he went.

228
00:20:49,487 --> 00:20:52,934
Pacquette, I want a dossier
on every Chinaman in that box.

229
00:20:53,090 --> 00:20:54,433
Go, go, go, go, go.

230
00:21:02,033 --> 00:21:03,876
Inspector, it's awfully late and...

231
00:21:04,302 --> 00:21:06,873
Oh, I'm just going over
these crime-scene photos.

232
00:21:07,038 --> 00:21:10,508
- Don't you need some rest?
- Crime does not rest, Nicole.

233
00:21:10,675 --> 00:21:12,018
It's true.

234
00:21:12,176 --> 00:21:13,883
You see...

235
00:21:14,045 --> 00:21:16,525
I have waited a long time
to prove myself.

236
00:21:17,148 --> 00:21:19,788
And I've been given
the opportunity of a lifetime.

237
00:21:20,184 --> 00:21:23,597
And I intend to show the world
exactly who I am.

238
00:21:23,754 --> 00:21:27,065
And what I can do.
I must not fail.

239
00:21:28,192 --> 00:21:30,866
You won't. I know it.

240
00:21:31,028 --> 00:21:32,974
Thank you, Nicole.

241
00:21:36,467 --> 00:21:38,469
- Nicole?
- Yes?

242
00:21:38,803 --> 00:21:41,079
May I be very frank with you?

243
00:21:41,639 --> 00:21:42,879
Of course.

244
00:21:43,040 --> 00:21:45,680
You have put on a ton of weight.

245
00:21:45,843 --> 00:21:48,483
Now, what I do
when I get a little heavy...

246
00:21:50,815 --> 00:21:52,556
Never mind.

247
00:21:52,984 --> 00:21:55,328
Would you like me to stay behind
and help you?

248
00:21:57,622 --> 00:21:59,659
That is a generous offer, Nicole...

249
00:21:59,824 --> 00:22:03,465
but I am quite sensitive
to office gender politics.

250
00:22:03,628 --> 00:22:06,370
And in today's world,
the slightest gesture...

251
00:22:06,530 --> 00:22:09,909
can be misinterpreted
as harassment.

252
00:22:10,067 --> 00:22:14,174
And it is late, and I would prefer
not to put you or me...

253
00:22:14,338 --> 00:22:17,319
into that delicate situation.

254
00:22:17,475 --> 00:22:18,920
Agreed?

255
00:22:19,076 --> 00:22:20,578
Yes, I agree.

256
00:22:20,745 --> 00:22:24,318
Well, let's seal it with a kiss.
And I'll get back to work.

257
00:22:26,450 --> 00:22:27,952
I am going to be frank.

258
00:22:28,119 --> 00:22:30,190
Since you are only a detective,
second class...

259
00:22:30,354 --> 00:22:32,527
your senses may not be as sharp
as my own.

260
00:22:32,690 --> 00:22:35,170
And as I do not want a partner
who makes me duller...

261
00:22:35,326 --> 00:22:38,933
I have come up with a plan
to keep you as sharp as possible.

262
00:22:39,096 --> 00:22:40,769
And what is that?

263
00:22:40,931 --> 00:22:44,640
Intermittently, and without warning,
I will attack you...

264
00:22:44,802 --> 00:22:47,476
whenever and wherever
it is least expected.

265
00:22:47,905 --> 00:22:51,443
In this way, I will keep you
vigilant and alert. Agreed?

266
00:22:52,309 --> 00:22:53,617
Yes.

267
00:22:55,479 --> 00:22:58,119
- Good one.
- Thank you.

268
00:22:59,383 --> 00:23:00,919
Here we are.

269
00:23:06,824 --> 00:23:09,464
Do not open door
when light is flashing.

270
00:23:28,679 --> 00:23:30,454
Excuse me.

271
00:23:30,614 --> 00:23:33,026
Coming through. Thank you.

272
00:23:42,993 --> 00:23:44,802
And I'm wondering if you... Yes.

273
00:23:44,962 --> 00:23:48,432
I'm wondering if you saw, perhaps,
a person yelling.

274
00:23:48,599 --> 00:23:51,705
Stop! Stop, stop!

275
00:23:53,170 --> 00:23:55,172
Who are you,
and what the hell are you doing?

276
00:23:55,606 --> 00:23:58,553
- I'm in the middle of an interrogation.
- The booth is soundproof.

277
00:23:58,709 --> 00:24:01,280
She can't hear a word.
And in case you haven't noticed...

278
00:24:01,445 --> 00:24:03,789
You ruined my recording session.
Now, get out.

279
00:24:03,948 --> 00:24:06,622
Unless you want to be charged
with obstruction of justice...

280
00:24:06,784 --> 00:24:08,457
you will let me interrogate Xania.

281
00:24:08,619 --> 00:24:11,395
It's all right, Roland.
Hello, inspector.

282
00:24:11,555 --> 00:24:13,057
I'm Xania.

283
00:24:13,390 --> 00:24:17,236
You do not know this, but I am
intimately familiar with your work.

284
00:24:18,162 --> 00:24:20,142
You are very kind.

285
00:24:22,633 --> 00:24:24,738
Did you say that booth
was soundproof?

286
00:24:25,569 --> 00:24:26,809
Yes.

287
00:24:47,258 --> 00:24:50,728
Now, you were nearby
when Gluant was killed?

288
00:24:50,895 --> 00:24:53,603
Yes, I ran out to be with him
after the team won.

289
00:24:53,764 --> 00:24:55,004
Of course you did.

290
00:24:55,900 --> 00:24:57,504
Now, a few hours
before the murder...

291
00:24:57,835 --> 00:25:01,806
six witnesses saw you repeatedly
striking the deceased and screaming...

292
00:25:01,972 --> 00:25:03,383
What was it, Ponton?

293
00:25:03,541 --> 00:25:06,317
I am going to kill you.
I am going to kill you.

294
00:25:06,477 --> 00:25:09,924
I was angry.
I caught him with another woman.

295
00:25:10,080 --> 00:25:12,356
And this was after
he said he loved me.

296
00:25:12,516 --> 00:25:14,587
You poor little angel waif.

297
00:25:15,586 --> 00:25:17,827
After he cheated on me...

298
00:25:18,422 --> 00:25:20,333
I hated him.

299
00:25:20,758 --> 00:25:23,068
- But I didn't kill him.
- Of course you didn't.

300
00:25:23,227 --> 00:25:25,867
- You recently performed in China...
- Stop browbeating her!

301
00:25:26,030 --> 00:25:28,510
Can't you see she's sexy?

302
00:25:29,867 --> 00:25:31,642
Three months ago in Shanghai.

303
00:25:32,069 --> 00:25:35,278
Can you think of anyone else
who might have hated Gluant?

304
00:25:35,606 --> 00:25:38,416
- Bizu.
- The football star?

305
00:25:38,843 --> 00:25:42,052
I was dating Bizu when I met Gluant.

306
00:25:42,379 --> 00:25:45,383
He thought Gluant was a bad guy
for stealing me away.

307
00:25:45,549 --> 00:25:48,621
- If you ask me, they were both...
- You, don't leave town.

308
00:25:49,320 --> 00:25:51,732
But I'm flying to Montserrat
to record Rene Duchanel...

309
00:25:51,889 --> 00:25:55,063
You will not leave town. I may want
to ask you a few more questions.

310
00:25:55,326 --> 00:25:57,101
But I don't know anything.

311
00:25:57,261 --> 00:26:02,108
About life, about love.
Yes, you little wet puppy.

312
00:26:02,266 --> 00:26:04,507
But about the crime
you may know a lot.

313
00:26:04,668 --> 00:26:06,579
Inspector.

314
00:26:07,638 --> 00:26:09,311
Do I have to stay in town?

315
00:26:09,473 --> 00:26:11,248
Because next week
I have something...

316
00:26:12,509 --> 00:26:14,614
vague to do in New York.

317
00:26:14,945 --> 00:26:17,755
Well, if you absolutely have
to do something vague...

318
00:26:17,915 --> 00:26:19,485
feel free to go where you wish.

319
00:26:39,403 --> 00:26:43,180
I can't take you to Bizu, but I can
take you to Monsieur Vainqueur...

320
00:26:43,340 --> 00:26:45,820
the team's assistant coach.

321
00:26:45,976 --> 00:26:48,752
Well, I guess he's
the head coach now.

322
00:26:49,613 --> 00:26:51,923
- You wanted to see me?
- You are Vainqueur?

323
00:26:52,716 --> 00:26:55,219
Yes. And who are you?

324
00:26:55,386 --> 00:26:58,333
I am Inspector Clouseau.
Perhaps you have heard of me.

325
00:26:58,489 --> 00:26:59,832
No.

326
00:27:00,591 --> 00:27:01,831
Don't write that down.

327
00:27:03,427 --> 00:27:06,738
- What do you want?
- I am told that Bizu hated Gluant.

328
00:27:07,031 --> 00:27:09,443
A lot of people hated Gluant.

329
00:27:09,600 --> 00:27:11,307
Did you?

330
00:27:11,468 --> 00:27:15,211
I spent six years under his thumb
being verbally abused every day.

331
00:27:15,372 --> 00:27:17,409
Yes, I was not a fan
of Yves Gluant.

332
00:27:17,574 --> 00:27:19,383
And now he is dead...

333
00:27:19,543 --> 00:27:21,489
and you have his job.

334
00:27:21,645 --> 00:27:23,283
Ironic.

335
00:27:23,447 --> 00:27:25,449
Not every death is a tragedy.

336
00:27:25,616 --> 00:27:29,860
- And what was the...?
- Footsteps.

337
00:27:30,020 --> 00:27:31,590
It's a young woman...

338
00:27:31,755 --> 00:27:33,894
30 to 35 years old...

339
00:27:34,058 --> 00:27:37,232
5'2", 5'4", brunette.

340
00:27:37,394 --> 00:27:39,670
And she is wearing high heels.

341
00:27:39,830 --> 00:27:42,936
Perhaps a bit too formal
for the afternoon.

342
00:27:43,100 --> 00:27:45,137
And she has on...

343
00:27:45,536 --> 00:27:48,210
Chanel N°5.

344
00:27:54,511 --> 00:27:56,923
- Is anyone with you?
- No.

345
00:27:57,281 --> 00:27:59,727
Do you have a pair of high heels
in that bag?

346
00:27:59,883 --> 00:28:02,864
- No.
- Not even a small pair of pumps?

347
00:28:03,520 --> 00:28:05,466
- No.
- Who are you?

348
00:28:05,622 --> 00:28:07,693
I am Yuri, the trainer.

349
00:28:07,858 --> 00:28:10,566
And what is it you do here,
Yuri the trainer?

350
00:28:11,595 --> 00:28:12,835
I train.

351
00:28:12,997 --> 00:28:15,841
So you are Yuri the trainer
who trains.

352
00:28:20,804 --> 00:28:22,147
Do not leave Europe.

353
00:28:23,073 --> 00:28:24,882
But I have to go to Asia.

354
00:28:25,576 --> 00:28:26,987
Okay.

355
00:28:27,144 --> 00:28:28,748
Do not leave Europe or Asia.

356
00:28:30,381 --> 00:28:33,021
We have one match in Brazil.

357
00:28:33,183 --> 00:28:34,457
All right.

358
00:28:34,618 --> 00:28:38,031
Do not leave Europe, Asia
or the Americas.

359
00:28:39,690 --> 00:28:42,899
- Okay.
- Where is this famous soccer player?

360
00:28:43,060 --> 00:28:46,007
He is outside on the practice field.

361
00:28:46,330 --> 00:28:49,743
Well, we shall see about Mr. Bizu.

362
00:28:58,709 --> 00:29:00,814
I've got Bizu
in the interrogation room.

363
00:29:00,978 --> 00:29:02,013
What's the plan?

364
00:29:02,179 --> 00:29:05,524
I'm going to give him the
good-cop bad-cop routine.

365
00:29:07,284 --> 00:29:09,230
You are the soccer player
known as Bizu?

366
00:29:09,386 --> 00:29:12,128
- Yes.
- You were acquainted with Gluant?

367
00:29:12,756 --> 00:29:16,932
- I'm glad he's pushing up daisies.
- He is not pushing up daisies.

368
00:29:17,094 --> 00:29:18,437
He is dead.

369
00:29:19,396 --> 00:29:20,636
It's an idiom.

370
00:29:20,798 --> 00:29:24,371
You, sir, are the idiom.

371
00:29:24,535 --> 00:29:27,778
Now, unless you want to spend
the rest of your life in prison...

372
00:29:27,938 --> 00:29:31,317
You will answer the next question.
Did you kill him?

373
00:29:31,809 --> 00:29:34,551
I would have loved
to have killed him.

374
00:29:35,813 --> 00:29:38,692
But some lucky bastard
beat me to it.

375
00:29:39,416 --> 00:29:41,919
You disgust me.

376
00:29:42,286 --> 00:29:44,527
I'll be right back.

377
00:29:49,560 --> 00:29:50,800
Cigarette?

378
00:29:51,895 --> 00:29:53,465
No.

379
00:29:53,831 --> 00:29:54,866
Thanks.

380
00:29:55,365 --> 00:29:56,935
Good for you.

381
00:29:59,036 --> 00:30:00,674
Bizu...

382
00:30:03,841 --> 00:30:05,343
I know you didn't do it.

383
00:30:05,509 --> 00:30:08,080
Someone else did,
and they are trying to set you up.

384
00:30:08,612 --> 00:30:09,852
You'll help me?

385
00:30:10,414 --> 00:30:12,257
Of course I'll help you.

386
00:30:12,416 --> 00:30:16,489
Now, do you have any idea who
might have done this terrible thing?

387
00:30:16,653 --> 00:30:20,260
His partner in those
stupid restaurants, Larocque.

388
00:30:20,757 --> 00:30:23,567
Raymond Larocque,
the casino owner.

389
00:30:23,727 --> 00:30:26,731
Gluant would steal money from
the restaurants and use it to gamble.

390
00:30:27,064 --> 00:30:29,442
My guess is Larocque got fed up...

391
00:30:29,700 --> 00:30:31,236
and had him killed.

392
00:30:31,401 --> 00:30:34,007
Bizu, I like you.

393
00:30:34,171 --> 00:30:36,117
I'm going to help you.

394
00:30:36,273 --> 00:30:39,516
You and I are going to make
a great team.

395
00:30:46,116 --> 00:30:48,892
The good-cop bad-cop routine
is working perfectly.

396
00:30:49,052 --> 00:30:52,431
You know, usually
two different cops do that.

397
00:31:11,808 --> 00:31:16,188
You know what we do to prisoners
who don't cooperate?

398
00:31:16,346 --> 00:31:18,519
We hook them up to the box.

399
00:31:20,551 --> 00:31:22,827
What is the box?

400
00:31:23,520 --> 00:31:27,366
Idiot. Like this,
I take one electrode...

401
00:31:27,524 --> 00:31:29,470
I put it here.

402
00:31:31,395 --> 00:31:33,705
I take the other one...

403
00:31:33,864 --> 00:31:35,104
I put it...

404
00:31:48,445 --> 00:31:50,857
So, what do you think?

405
00:31:51,014 --> 00:31:53,085
Bizu is innocent.

406
00:31:53,517 --> 00:31:55,258
How can you say that?

407
00:31:55,419 --> 00:31:58,229
Gluant suspended Bizu.
He stole his girlfriend.

408
00:31:58,755 --> 00:32:02,703
If it were me, I would have killed him
then and there.

409
00:32:02,859 --> 00:32:04,668
That's exactly what Bizu did.

410
00:32:04,828 --> 00:32:06,432
Ponton...

411
00:32:06,597 --> 00:32:08,508
a crime is like a jigsaw puzzle.

412
00:32:08,665 --> 00:32:11,111
You have to have the jig
and you have to have the saw.

413
00:32:11,268 --> 00:32:13,077
You have the jig, but no saw.

414
00:32:13,237 --> 00:32:14,944
Where is your saw?

415
00:32:15,105 --> 00:32:18,382
Oh, Your Honor, I want to present
a case, but all I have is a jig.

416
00:32:18,542 --> 00:32:19,782
Is that okay?

417
00:32:23,714 --> 00:32:25,193
What?

418
00:32:25,616 --> 00:32:26,856
Nothing.

419
00:32:27,017 --> 00:32:28,496
I thought you said...

420
00:32:31,421 --> 00:32:32,832
No.

421
00:32:41,565 --> 00:32:43,511
Strange.

422
00:32:58,548 --> 00:33:00,585
Oh, it's you.

423
00:34:10,854 --> 00:34:13,460
I hope you don't mind I let
myself in with the spare key.

424
00:34:13,623 --> 00:34:16,229
- Oh, no, no.
- And, look.

425
00:34:17,994 --> 00:34:19,996
I got your pants back from the tailor.

426
00:34:20,163 --> 00:34:22,803
- Plus a spare.
- Good.

427
00:34:22,966 --> 00:34:25,845
- Would you like some water?
- Yes, please.

428
00:34:27,904 --> 00:34:33,411
You know, Nicole, this crime
is forcing me to use all my knowledge.

429
00:34:33,577 --> 00:34:37,923
Everything I have learned in a lifetime
of investigating is coming into play.

430
00:34:38,515 --> 00:34:41,189
Do you mind if I have these?
I haven't eaten.

431
00:34:41,351 --> 00:34:43,331
Oh, please, go ahead.

432
00:34:43,487 --> 00:34:47,993
Things are appearing in my mind
that I did not even realize was there.

433
00:34:48,158 --> 00:34:49,660
And yet the in...

434
00:34:49,826 --> 00:34:52,466
Oh, my God. The Heimlich!
The Heimlich!

435
00:35:10,414 --> 00:35:12,451
Are you feeling better?

436
00:35:12,949 --> 00:35:14,690
Yes, thank you.
You are so good at it.

437
00:35:14,851 --> 00:35:16,091
Where did you learn that?

438
00:35:16,253 --> 00:35:18,995
I used to practice on mannequins,
pillows...

439
00:35:19,156 --> 00:35:21,534
but frankly, it was the expression
on your face...

440
00:35:21,691 --> 00:35:23,568
that told me that you needed it.

441
00:35:23,727 --> 00:35:26,367
Now, Ponton, what do you
have for me?

442
00:35:26,530 --> 00:35:30,535
It seems you were right about Bizu.
He was just found dead...

443
00:35:30,700 --> 00:35:33,010
in the training facility locker room.

444
00:35:33,170 --> 00:35:35,844
- Shot in the head.
- Was it fatal?

445
00:35:36,006 --> 00:35:38,247
- Yes.
- How fatal?

446
00:35:39,142 --> 00:35:40,382
Completely.

447
00:35:40,744 --> 00:35:42,189
I want to talk to him now.

448
00:35:42,612 --> 00:35:44,148
He's dead.

449
00:35:50,120 --> 00:35:51,997
You there. Halt.

450
00:35:54,357 --> 00:35:56,428
You are Yuri the trainer
who trains.

451
00:35:56,593 --> 00:35:57,936
Yeah, that's right.

452
00:35:58,094 --> 00:36:01,598
I am looking for a dead body.
Perhaps you can tell me where it is.

453
00:36:01,765 --> 00:36:04,439
Oh, yeah. I heard it was
in the locker room.

454
00:36:04,601 --> 00:36:08,515
You go down the hall,
make a right and two lefts.

455
00:36:11,775 --> 00:36:14,051
You are finding
something amusing here?

456
00:36:14,211 --> 00:36:15,849
I'll be honest with you. I...

457
00:36:16,012 --> 00:36:18,151
I find your accent quite funny.

458
00:36:18,315 --> 00:36:20,886
- Where are you from?
- From Russia.

459
00:36:21,418 --> 00:36:24,627
Gluant recruited me
from the Russian military gym.

460
00:36:27,157 --> 00:36:28,602
You need to work on your accent.

461
00:36:29,025 --> 00:36:30,470
- What?
- What?

462
00:36:30,927 --> 00:36:32,600
- What? What?
- What?

463
00:36:32,762 --> 00:36:34,435
- What?
- I don't have time for this.

464
00:36:34,598 --> 00:36:35,872
I have to solve a murder.

465
00:36:40,036 --> 00:36:42,312
Please, tell me what you saw.

466
00:36:42,472 --> 00:36:45,248
Well, I didn't see anything.

467
00:36:45,742 --> 00:36:47,619
I was passing by the locker room.

468
00:36:47,777 --> 00:36:50,553
It was late, past time
anyone should be there.

469
00:36:50,714 --> 00:36:53,820
I heard movement on the other side
of the locker-room door.

470
00:36:53,984 --> 00:36:56,362
I heard Bizu say...

471
00:36:56,520 --> 00:36:59,763
Oh, it's you.

472
00:37:00,190 --> 00:37:02,864
And then there was gunfire.

473
00:37:03,026 --> 00:37:05,700
Ponton, go to your databases.

474
00:37:05,862 --> 00:37:10,504
I want to interrogate every person
in Paris with the name "You".

475
00:37:11,601 --> 00:37:13,046
And, Ponton...

476
00:37:13,570 --> 00:37:15,572
don't you find it
a bit of a coincidence...

477
00:37:15,739 --> 00:37:19,983
that the body fell perfectly
within the chalk outline on the floor?

478
00:37:20,477 --> 00:37:23,788
I think they drew
the chalk outline later.

479
00:37:24,314 --> 00:37:27,818
We are dealing
with some kind of mastermind.

480
00:37:27,984 --> 00:37:31,864
Ponton, I want to interrogate
this man Raymond Larocque.

481
00:37:32,022 --> 00:37:33,695
Where is his casino?

482
00:37:45,001 --> 00:37:49,108
Park it close by. Unless you want
to know what else is good for you.

483
00:37:50,373 --> 00:37:52,182
You continue to surprise me,
inspector.

484
00:37:52,342 --> 00:37:57,189
Get used to it, Ponton. With me,
surprises are rarely unexpected.

485
00:38:00,183 --> 00:38:04,097
Yes, the weather is nice today.
Let's hope it continues.

486
00:38:04,254 --> 00:38:06,530
Ponton, go find security.

487
00:38:06,690 --> 00:38:10,160
Tell them I want to converse
with Mr. Raymond Larocque.

488
00:38:10,327 --> 00:38:13,797
- You're not coming?
- Something has come up.

489
00:38:13,964 --> 00:38:18,572
If the weather stays this mild,
we are all in for a treat.

490
00:38:18,735 --> 00:38:23,411
- Place your bets.
- I am in law enforcement too.

491
00:38:23,840 --> 00:38:25,114
Am I that obvious?

492
00:38:25,275 --> 00:38:29,690
No, it's just that I have an ear
for such things.

493
00:38:30,080 --> 00:38:32,219
Here is your mojito.

494
00:38:32,649 --> 00:38:35,357
- Flame it.
- No more bets.

495
00:38:39,589 --> 00:38:41,125
Impressive.

496
00:38:41,291 --> 00:38:43,498
I will remember that.

497
00:38:44,527 --> 00:38:48,407
I am Inspector Jacques Clouseau.
I am here on a very important case.

498
00:38:48,565 --> 00:38:51,512
Boswell. Nigel Boswell.
Agent 006.

499
00:38:51,668 --> 00:38:53,670
- Know what that means?
- Of course I do.

500
00:38:53,837 --> 00:38:55,407
You are one short of the big time.

501
00:38:57,240 --> 00:38:59,345
I, too, am on a very important case,
inspector.

502
00:38:59,509 --> 00:39:01,614
So you understand
what I mean when I say...

503
00:39:01,778 --> 00:39:04,088
no one must know that I am here.

504
00:39:04,247 --> 00:39:06,887
I have just slipped my
cell-phone number into your pocket.

505
00:39:09,052 --> 00:39:10,554
Call me if you need any help.

506
00:39:11,321 --> 00:39:13,528
I will, inspector.

507
00:39:25,235 --> 00:39:26,475
Well...

508
00:39:26,636 --> 00:39:29,515
Monet. Very impressive,
Monsieur Larocque.

509
00:39:29,673 --> 00:39:31,243
Very impressive,
Inspector Clouseau.

510
00:39:31,408 --> 00:39:33,820
Please make yourself at home.
Now, how can I help you?

511
00:39:33,977 --> 00:39:37,049
I am investigating the murder
of Yves Gluant.

512
00:39:37,280 --> 00:39:38,918
Yves.

513
00:39:39,315 --> 00:39:40,919
Fascinating man.

514
00:39:41,084 --> 00:39:44,793
Would you happen to know
what he paid for the Pink Panther?

515
00:39:44,954 --> 00:39:47,161
He inherited it.
It cost him nothing.

516
00:39:47,624 --> 00:39:49,297
It cost him his life.

517
00:39:51,828 --> 00:39:54,331
I would like to take a closer look
at your bowls.

518
00:39:55,231 --> 00:39:58,007
- My what?
- Your bowls.

519
00:39:58,168 --> 00:39:59,841
I would like to take a closer look...

520
00:40:00,003 --> 00:40:02,313
at your big brass bowls.

521
00:40:06,042 --> 00:40:08,682
- Okay.
- Thank you.

522
00:40:11,081 --> 00:40:12,617
Han Dynasty.

523
00:40:12,782 --> 00:40:15,558
- Very rare. Beautiful.
- I see you have an eye for antiques.

524
00:40:15,752 --> 00:40:18,460
Some here are real
and some are copies.

525
00:40:18,655 --> 00:40:20,328
I'm sure you can tell
which are which.

526
00:40:20,490 --> 00:40:23,232
Second century. Very rare.

527
00:40:23,760 --> 00:40:26,832
One should always handle
an antique vase from the inside.

528
00:40:26,996 --> 00:40:31,138
Otherwise the oil from the hands
can damage the patina.

529
00:40:32,502 --> 00:40:34,448
Pure alabaster.

530
00:40:34,604 --> 00:40:36,174
Lovely.

531
00:40:42,312 --> 00:40:46,454
That's odd. What I did,
I went like this, and then...

532
00:40:53,923 --> 00:40:56,403
This is weird.

533
00:40:59,395 --> 00:41:02,399
Why did you take out
a life-insurance policy on Gluant?

534
00:41:02,565 --> 00:41:06,342
The insurance company won't pay
unless the murderer is caught.

535
00:41:06,503 --> 00:41:08,847
And if it turns out to be me...

536
00:41:09,005 --> 00:41:11,315
they won't pay at all.
Do you understand?

537
00:41:11,975 --> 00:41:14,956
But you stood to gain
from Gluant's death, didn't you?

538
00:41:15,111 --> 00:41:17,421
Gain? What would I gain?

539
00:41:17,881 --> 00:41:20,384
Gluant's share of the restaurants.

540
00:41:20,550 --> 00:41:22,689
Oh, the restaurants
were a disaster.

541
00:41:23,253 --> 00:41:26,291
Gluant was siphoning money out
faster than it came in.

542
00:41:26,456 --> 00:41:30,063
My only consolation was he'd lose
the money gambling in my casino.

543
00:41:30,460 --> 00:41:33,100
But after a while his losses
became so ridiculous...

544
00:41:33,263 --> 00:41:35,903
he promised me his ring
as collateral.

545
00:41:36,733 --> 00:41:39,043
But someone had words
with Gluant...

546
00:41:39,202 --> 00:41:40,806
the night before he was killed.

547
00:41:41,271 --> 00:41:43,842
- Didn't you?
- No.

548
00:41:44,340 --> 00:41:48,584
You didn't threaten to break his legs
and then crush him into powder?

549
00:41:48,978 --> 00:41:50,218
No.

550
00:41:51,347 --> 00:41:53,190
Perhaps I saw that on TV.

551
00:41:58,087 --> 00:42:01,364
Well, I can certainly think
of a better place for this.

552
00:42:05,862 --> 00:42:08,570
That's my personalized
cell-phone tone ring.

553
00:42:15,171 --> 00:42:16,479
Hello?

554
00:42:16,639 --> 00:42:18,141
Yes, this is Inspector...

555
00:42:18,608 --> 00:42:21,020
Yes, I could meet you.
In the restaurant?

556
00:42:21,711 --> 00:42:23,247
Yes, of course. Right away.

557
00:42:23,413 --> 00:42:27,020
Gentlemen, something has come up.
Please excuse me.

558
00:42:27,183 --> 00:42:28,457
- Monsieur Larocque.
- Yes.

559
00:42:28,618 --> 00:42:30,029
Is this vase of great value?

560
00:42:30,386 --> 00:42:32,263
It is a worthless imitation.

561
00:42:32,422 --> 00:42:33,992
Good.

562
00:42:36,559 --> 00:42:38,732
But that desk was...

563
00:42:38,895 --> 00:42:40,135
priceless.

564
00:42:46,502 --> 00:42:48,175
- Clouseau.
- Oh, yes.

565
00:42:48,338 --> 00:42:51,285
I need your help. Now, it's very
important that you remain calm.

566
00:42:51,441 --> 00:42:54,354
- And you do not turn around.
- Remain calm. Do not turn around.

567
00:42:54,510 --> 00:42:56,820
Behind you in the casino
are the Gas Mask Bandits.

568
00:42:57,480 --> 00:43:00,120
Oh, my God!
The Gas Mask Bandits!

569
00:43:01,084 --> 00:43:03,223
- All Europe is looking for them.
- How can I help?

570
00:43:03,386 --> 00:43:06,265
- Just give me your coat.
- Yes, of course. Why?

571
00:43:06,422 --> 00:43:07,992
I'm not supposed to be here.

572
00:43:08,157 --> 00:43:10,535
But I can't let
the Gas Mask Bandits escape.

573
00:43:49,933 --> 00:43:53,176
- Put it on.
- Yes. Yes, of course. But why?

574
00:43:53,670 --> 00:43:56,480
I'm not supposed to be here,
remember?

575
00:43:58,041 --> 00:43:59,520
Inspector.

576
00:44:01,010 --> 00:44:03,183
My God, man, that was fantastic.

577
00:44:10,586 --> 00:44:13,692
Inspector, was Clouseau's plan to set
a trap for the Gas Mask Bandits?

578
00:44:13,856 --> 00:44:16,837
Does Clouseau think the Bandits
are connected to the Pink Panther?

579
00:44:16,993 --> 00:44:18,734
Is Clouseau
going to be promoted, sir?

580
00:44:18,895 --> 00:44:23,139
I cannot comment
on ongoing investigations.

581
00:44:23,299 --> 00:44:24,539
Drive.

582
00:44:26,336 --> 00:44:27,974
Inspector?

583
00:44:28,371 --> 00:44:29,611
Clouseau?

584
00:44:33,476 --> 00:44:34,887
Good one.

585
00:44:35,044 --> 00:44:36,546
Thank you.

586
00:44:36,713 --> 00:44:38,693
Now, what do you have for me?

587
00:44:38,848 --> 00:44:40,953
We have rounded up
all the people in Paris...

588
00:44:41,117 --> 00:44:45,065
- with the name "You".
- Finally, we are getting somewhere.

589
00:44:59,769 --> 00:45:01,578
Read that back.

590
00:45:06,042 --> 00:45:07,715
You may go.

591
00:45:09,979 --> 00:45:10,980
You speak Chinese?

592
