What, you don't think
I speak Chinese?

593
00:45:14,117 --> 00:45:16,290
If I don't speak Chinese,
what are we doing here?

594
00:45:16,619 --> 00:45:18,599
That must be funny
around the water cooler.

595
00:45:18,755 --> 00:45:20,860
Oh, Inspector Clouseau
does not speak Chinese.

596
00:45:21,024 --> 00:45:23,504
Let's take him out for lunch.
We will all speak Chinese.

597
00:45:23,659 --> 00:45:25,468
He won't know
what we are talking about.

598
00:45:25,628 --> 00:45:28,165
Is that what you like to do?
Is that funny?

599
00:45:28,331 --> 00:45:30,607
Of course I speak Chinese.

600
00:45:35,938 --> 00:45:37,645
Clouseau?

601
00:46:04,801 --> 00:46:06,610
Bonjour, Nicole.

602
00:46:06,969 --> 00:46:09,279
Could I see you in my office
in a few minutes?

603
00:46:09,439 --> 00:46:12,420
I'll be right with you, inspector.

604
00:46:40,103 --> 00:46:41,343
Yes, inspector?

605
00:46:42,138 --> 00:46:43,378
Nicole.

606
00:46:43,539 --> 00:46:46,850
The weather has been so pleasant.

607
00:46:47,009 --> 00:46:52,152
I was wondering if you think
it's going to stay this mild.

608
00:46:53,316 --> 00:46:56,160
I certainly hope so.

609
00:46:57,687 --> 00:47:00,600
But do you think the weather...

610
00:47:00,756 --> 00:47:03,327
is going to change?

611
00:47:03,826 --> 00:47:05,999
Let's keep our fingers crossed...

612
00:47:06,162 --> 00:47:08,733
that it stays this mild.

613
00:47:09,999 --> 00:47:12,309
And here's another one for you!

614
00:47:14,036 --> 00:47:15,777
Now let's see who you are.

615
00:47:17,673 --> 00:47:20,119
It is Inspector Dreyfus.

616
00:47:20,276 --> 00:47:22,916
The intruder is obviously wearing
a flesh mask.

617
00:47:23,079 --> 00:47:24,581
But that will come off.

618
00:47:26,449 --> 00:47:28,451
My face!

619
00:47:33,022 --> 00:47:35,195
Maybe there is a seam
under your hairline.

620
00:47:35,358 --> 00:47:37,269
I'll just turn you around.

621
00:47:44,367 --> 00:47:47,541
Are you feeling any better?
I am so sorry, inspector.

622
00:47:48,337 --> 00:47:50,112
Let's just forget it.

623
00:47:50,273 --> 00:47:53,686
I thought I would stop by and let you
know how we are doing on the case.

624
00:47:53,843 --> 00:47:56,221
Oh, I'll just...

625
00:47:56,379 --> 00:47:59,588
- stay back here.
- Yes, of course.

626
00:48:00,082 --> 00:48:03,029
I see you have one
of these collapsible pointers.

627
00:48:03,186 --> 00:48:04,426
So very useful.

628
00:48:04,587 --> 00:48:07,431
It is so degrading to have to point
with your finger...

629
00:48:07,590 --> 00:48:09,763
or one of those
long wooden sticks...

630
00:48:09,926 --> 00:48:12,736
like you are some sort
of primitive oaf.

631
00:48:12,895 --> 00:48:17,935
But you have one of these, you just
snap it open and you are ready to go.

632
00:48:18,100 --> 00:48:19,943
The case. The case, Clouseau.

633
00:48:20,269 --> 00:48:22,476
Yes, the case.

634
00:48:22,638 --> 00:48:26,643
The case is going quite well.
I have prepared a list of suspects.

635
00:48:27,643 --> 00:48:29,782
And how many suspects
do you have?

636
00:48:30,313 --> 00:48:32,793
Twenty-seven thousand
six hundred eighty-three.

637
00:48:33,716 --> 00:48:36,754
It's just a matter of time now,
isn't it?

638
00:48:36,919 --> 00:48:40,298
- Have you eliminated any suspects?
- Yes.

639
00:48:40,890 --> 00:48:42,164
One.

640
00:48:42,725 --> 00:48:44,830
One. And who would that be?

641
00:48:45,795 --> 00:48:47,035
Gluant.

642
00:48:48,231 --> 00:48:50,472
Gluant is the victim.

643
00:48:51,067 --> 00:48:53,308
Excellent, inspector.

644
00:48:53,469 --> 00:48:55,449
We think alike.

645
00:48:55,972 --> 00:49:00,284
One clue leading inexorably
to the next.

646
00:49:02,345 --> 00:49:03,585
Just leave it.

647
00:49:05,915 --> 00:49:07,394
I assure you, inspector...

648
00:49:07,783 --> 00:49:11,196
I will soon have your criminal
cornered like a...

649
00:49:11,354 --> 00:49:13,857
like a, like... like a, like...

650
00:49:14,023 --> 00:49:17,095
like something...
something that you... you corner.

651
00:49:17,460 --> 00:49:20,600
- Well put.
- I see you enjoy wordplay.

652
00:49:20,763 --> 00:49:22,470
We will have to have lunch
one day...

653
00:49:22,632 --> 00:49:25,875
and engage
in a little verbal jousting.

654
00:49:26,535 --> 00:49:29,015
I'm sure you're quite the raconteur.

655
00:49:31,907 --> 00:49:33,215
Yes.

656
00:49:34,744 --> 00:49:37,350
So I will call you for lunch.

657
00:49:41,317 --> 00:49:44,230
There's only one item
on the agenda of this committee.

658
00:49:44,887 --> 00:49:49,029
To approve the list of nominees
for our nation's highest award.

659
00:49:49,191 --> 00:49:50,670
The Medal of Honor.

660
00:49:50,826 --> 00:49:53,170
The two nominees are...

661
00:49:53,629 --> 00:49:54,937
Charles Dreyfus...

662
00:49:57,566 --> 00:49:58,909
No.

663
00:50:00,636 --> 00:50:02,843
And Sister Marie-Hugette...

664
00:50:03,839 --> 00:50:06,752
whose selfless concern
for our nation's orphans...

665
00:50:06,909 --> 00:50:09,321
is an inspiration to us all.

666
00:50:09,478 --> 00:50:12,891
I would like to add one more name
for the committee's consideration.

667
00:50:13,049 --> 00:50:16,553
Inspector Jacques Clouseau, the man
who came here from a small village...

668
00:50:16,719 --> 00:50:18,824
to investigate the murder
of Yves Gluant...

669
00:50:18,988 --> 00:50:22,231
who just last night captured
the notorious Gas Mask Bandits.

670
00:50:22,391 --> 00:50:25,372
Yes. Interesting idea.

671
00:50:26,295 --> 00:50:28,297
- An average Frenchman.
- Exactly.

672
00:50:28,464 --> 00:50:30,341
Excellent idea.

673
00:50:30,499 --> 00:50:32,740
All in favor?

674
00:50:32,902 --> 00:50:36,315
How is it I was not informed
of Clouseau's going to that casino?

675
00:50:36,472 --> 00:50:40,010
- It was the middle of the night.
- Oh, it was the middle of the night.

676
00:50:40,176 --> 00:50:42,417
What, you did not want to wake me?

677
00:50:42,578 --> 00:50:44,489
I want to know
of Clouseau's whereabouts...

678
00:50:44,647 --> 00:50:46,957
every hour, 24 hours a day.

679
00:50:47,116 --> 00:50:49,790
You miss one call, and I will have
you kicked off the force.

680
00:50:49,952 --> 00:50:52,489
- Do you understand?
- Yes, sir.

681
00:50:52,655 --> 00:50:55,101
Why are you not with him now?

682
00:50:55,257 --> 00:50:58,602
- I'm here.
- Get out.

683
00:51:01,630 --> 00:51:03,940
- Clouseau.
- Ponton.

684
00:51:04,100 --> 00:51:06,512
Let's call it a day. I am tired.

685
00:51:06,669 --> 00:51:09,548
I just wanted to see where you are
with the investigation.

686
00:51:09,705 --> 00:51:12,151
Good idea, Ponton.
To let the subconscious mind...

687
00:51:12,308 --> 00:51:15,289
work on the case while we sleep.
Now then, what are the facts?

688
00:51:15,478 --> 00:51:16,752
Yves Gluant was found...

689
00:51:16,912 --> 00:51:19,222
at the international championship
semifinal...

690
00:51:19,382 --> 00:51:22,124
- with a poison dart in his neck.
- The crime!

691
00:51:22,284 --> 00:51:25,094
Bizu wanted to kill him,
but is now himself dead.

692
00:51:25,254 --> 00:51:26,733
A complication!

693
00:51:26,889 --> 00:51:28,368
Gluant was siphoning off money...

694
00:51:28,524 --> 00:51:30,265
- from Larocque.
- A motive!

695
00:51:30,426 --> 00:51:32,565
And close to the body
was the singer, Xania.

696
00:51:32,995 --> 00:51:34,406
Xania is not the killer.

697
00:51:34,563 --> 00:51:36,907
But I suspect she knows more
than she is telling me.

698
00:51:37,066 --> 00:51:39,876
- Where is she now?
- She left suddenly for New York.

699
00:51:40,035 --> 00:51:43,642
