757
00:55:18,787 --> 00:55:20,323
Oh, no.

758
00:55:20,489 --> 00:55:23,368
Love has not yet come my way.

759
00:55:23,525 --> 00:55:26,529
How could Inspector Clouseau
be with a simple woman?

760
00:55:26,695 --> 00:55:31,007
She would have to be
so extraordinary in order to keep up.

761
00:55:31,834 --> 00:55:33,472
It's hard.

762
00:55:37,673 --> 00:55:41,246
- What is?
- For you to meet someone.

763
00:55:41,810 --> 00:55:43,790
Oh, yes.

764
00:55:44,747 --> 00:55:46,954
We have a big day tomorrow.

765
00:55:47,116 --> 00:55:51,861
We will go to Xania's hotel
and find out what she is up to.

766
00:55:52,488 --> 00:55:55,469
- Good night, Ponton.
- Good night, Clouseau.

767
00:55:56,392 --> 00:55:57,962
- Good one.
- Thank you.

768
00:56:03,699 --> 00:56:05,701
I got her hotel phone records.

769
00:56:05,868 --> 00:56:07,438
Xania made two phone calls...

770
00:56:07,603 --> 00:56:10,277
to a notorious
black-market diamond cutter.

771
00:56:10,839 --> 00:56:13,046
There she is! Newspapers!

772
00:56:18,914 --> 00:56:20,587
Newspapers!

773
00:56:23,285 --> 00:56:24,958
Newspapers!

774
00:56:26,955 --> 00:56:28,229
Newspapers!

775
00:56:48,410 --> 00:56:50,447
Floor 12.

776
00:56:53,282 --> 00:56:56,229
I smell something fishy.

777
00:57:00,622 --> 00:57:02,431
May I help you?

778
00:57:16,872 --> 00:57:18,943
Good teamwork.

779
00:57:27,816 --> 00:57:31,491
Stop! Stop whatever it is
you are doing! You are defenseless!

780
00:57:31,653 --> 00:57:34,600
We have already taken care
of your thugs patrolling the building.

781
00:57:34,757 --> 00:57:36,464
I don't have any thugs.

782
00:57:36,625 --> 00:57:38,229
You don't?

783
00:57:38,694 --> 00:57:42,301
Ponton, I think we owe
those men an apology.

784
00:57:42,464 --> 00:57:44,705
And what is it you are cutting?

785
00:57:45,134 --> 00:57:47,171
Pink diamond. Clear.

786
00:57:47,369 --> 00:57:50,680
- Clear?
- It's not the Pink Panther.

787
00:57:51,940 --> 00:57:54,887
And what are you doing here
sneaking around?

788
00:57:55,911 --> 00:57:58,585
This purse once belonged
to Josephine Baker.

789
00:57:58,747 --> 00:58:01,557
It was falling apart, so
I had it studded with diamonds...

790
00:58:01,717 --> 00:58:03,719
to wear on-stage
at the Presidential Ball.

791
00:58:03,919 --> 00:58:06,627
Well, why did you just not tell me
why you were coming?

792
00:58:07,222 --> 00:58:09,759
I can't be seen at a diamond cutter.

793
00:58:09,925 --> 00:58:11,802
Not after what happened.

794
00:58:14,229 --> 00:58:18,075
That may be one
of your mysterious clients now.

795
00:58:18,433 --> 00:58:19,969
Hello?

796
00:58:20,369 --> 00:58:23,907
Yes, I am the person
in charge of the phone bill.

797
00:58:24,072 --> 00:58:26,143
Well, I'm somewhat happy
with my service.

798
00:58:26,308 --> 00:58:28,345
Twelve months
with that many minutes?

799
00:58:28,510 --> 00:58:30,490
Plus free minutes per month?

800
00:58:30,913 --> 00:58:33,917
Yes, sign me up.
Yes, Jacques Clouseau.

801
00:58:34,082 --> 00:58:36,460
Credit card number...

802
00:58:49,965 --> 00:58:53,708
Yes? Yes, you may have
my e-mail address.

803
00:58:54,536 --> 00:58:58,416
DoctorKnockers@aol.com.

804
00:58:59,741 --> 00:59:03,780
Well, I think I just got myself
a pretty good deal.

805
00:59:07,749 --> 00:59:11,356
- When are you leaving the city?
- I'm leaving tomorrow. Yeah.

806
00:59:12,387 --> 00:59:15,596
I may have to seduce her, Ponton,
in order to get her to talk.

807
00:59:15,757 --> 00:59:17,759
- Part of the job.
- Talk about what?

808
00:59:17,926 --> 00:59:20,839
I want to find out what time
her plane is leaving in the morning.

809
00:59:20,996 --> 00:59:23,408
- Why not just ask her?
- Too obvious.

810
00:59:23,565 --> 00:59:26,171
I may have to pump her
for information.

811
00:59:26,335 --> 00:59:29,077
- I see.
- Inspector...

812
00:59:30,072 --> 00:59:33,212
would you like to join me
for dinner at the Waldorf?

813
00:59:33,775 --> 00:59:35,584
Certainly, mademoiselle.

814
00:59:35,744 --> 00:59:37,951
Say, 8:00?

815
00:59:38,547 --> 00:59:39,890
Eight o'clock.

816
00:59:40,249 --> 00:59:43,787
Say, I don't know,
my room on the second floor?

817
00:59:44,286 --> 00:59:47,495
I don't know,
my room on the second floor.

818
00:59:48,257 --> 00:59:49,634
I'll see you then.

819
00:59:52,194 --> 00:59:54,105
It might be a trap.

820
00:59:54,263 --> 00:59:56,243
Who cares?

821
01:00:14,049 --> 01:00:16,495
Welcome to my room, inspector.

822
01:00:17,619 --> 01:00:19,462
It is lovely weather we are having.

823
01:00:35,170 --> 01:00:38,743
Oh, yes, baby. Oh, yes.

824
01:00:47,749 --> 01:00:49,285
Why?

825
01:00:50,152 --> 01:00:51,460
Why what?

826
01:00:51,620 --> 01:00:55,432
Why were you being
so elusive today?

827
01:00:56,258 --> 01:00:58,135
I was afraid of Larocque.

828
01:00:58,293 --> 01:01:02,537
- He might be following me.
- Larocque? The casino owner?

829
01:01:02,698 --> 01:01:04,700
He sent out word
threatening to kill anyone...

830
01:01:04,866 --> 01:01:06,675
in possession
of the Pink Panther.

831
01:01:06,835 --> 01:01:08,837
He believes it belongs to him.

832
01:01:09,237 --> 01:01:10,807
But why would he follow you?

833
01:01:11,173 --> 01:01:13,915
I was in New York
to see a diamond cutter.

834
01:01:14,076 --> 01:01:15,987
He might draw
the wrong conclusion.

835
01:01:16,411 --> 01:01:17,788
You know...

836
01:01:17,946 --> 01:01:23,362
a man sitting here
in your private suite...

837
01:01:23,518 --> 01:01:25,520
so close to you...

838
01:01:25,687 --> 01:01:27,963
might draw
the wrong conclusion too.

839
01:01:28,457 --> 01:01:30,698
Or the right one.

840
01:01:31,493 --> 01:01:33,564
I've heard things
about you, inspector.

841
01:01:34,329 --> 01:01:36,172
What sort of things?

842
01:01:36,331 --> 01:01:38,777
That you really know
how to treat a woman.

843
01:01:44,940 --> 01:01:48,149
Yes. Yes.

844
01:01:48,643 --> 01:01:51,487
Let the games begin.

845
01:01:52,848 --> 01:01:55,920
Let me just slip away.

846
01:02:10,198 --> 01:02:11,871
Yes!

847
01:02:17,239 --> 01:02:19,412
No! No, no! No, no!

848
01:02:20,409 --> 01:02:23,447
My miracle pill
for the middle-aged man.

849
01:02:33,855 --> 01:02:35,129
Give it back.

850
01:02:49,204 --> 01:02:50,945
Inspector?

851
01:02:52,240 --> 01:02:57,280
- Are you all right in there?
- I hope you're getting yourself ready.

852
01:03:02,784 --> 01:03:04,786
Inspector? Are you sure
you're okay in there?

853
01:03:04,953 --> 01:03:08,196
Yes, I am. I'm fine.
I'm just getting in the mood for love.

854
01:03:37,519 --> 01:03:39,863
Well, hello.

855
01:03:47,829 --> 01:03:50,833
We need fresh towels in 204.

856
01:03:54,069 --> 01:03:57,346
Don't ask why, just do it.

857
01:03:57,506 --> 01:04:00,715
You have the flight number.
He leaves tomorrow out of JFK.

858
01:04:00,876 --> 01:04:05,120
He'll be easy to spot. He's got
white hair, a thin mustache...

859
01:04:05,280 --> 01:04:08,921
brimming with self-confidence
and completely lost.

860
01:04:17,592 --> 01:04:19,663
- Did you get the stuff?
- Yes.

861
01:04:19,828 --> 01:04:21,239
Good.

862
01:04:21,396 --> 01:04:25,469
Give it to me.
Airline food is for suckers.

863
01:04:25,634 --> 01:04:29,343
I will smuggle this on.
Just act cool.

864
01:04:36,077 --> 01:04:38,079
- Hey, that's Xania!
- Hello.

865
01:04:38,246 --> 01:04:40,624
Hi. Yes, thank you.

866
01:04:40,782 --> 01:04:43,262
I still think she is hiding
something, Ponton.

867
01:04:43,418 --> 01:04:44,726
What?

868
01:04:44,886 --> 01:04:47,924
If I knew what she was hiding,
then it wouldn't be hidden, would it?

869
01:04:48,089 --> 01:04:50,091
- All right. Thank you.
- One more! One more!

870
01:04:50,258 --> 01:04:51,669
Okay, let's go. Next.

871
01:04:51,826 --> 01:04:53,999
Nothing to declare.

872
01:04:57,732 --> 01:05:00,906
- Come on through.
- Hand check on two.

873
01:05:02,237 --> 01:05:04,274
- This your bag, sir?
- Yes, it is.

874
01:05:04,439 --> 01:05:07,545
- We'll have to hand check it.
- Go ahead. I have nothing to hide...

875
01:05:07,709 --> 01:05:09,086
in my bag.

876
01:05:09,711 --> 01:05:11,486
Come with me, sir.

877
01:05:13,114 --> 01:05:14,855
Wait here, pal.

878
01:05:25,627 --> 01:05:28,039
It's a harmless pocketknife.

879
01:05:32,834 --> 01:05:35,337
It's a harmless pair of
numchucks?

880
01:05:39,307 --> 01:05:42,777
I don't... I don't even own a mace.
I don't know where that came from.

881
01:05:48,950 --> 01:05:50,861
I've never seen that stuff in my life.

882
01:05:51,052 --> 01:05:52,725
Jimbo!

883
01:05:53,588 --> 01:05:56,000
You don't need Jimbo.

884
01:05:59,261 --> 01:06:01,537
- Jimbo, stay.
- What's in your pocket, sir?

885
01:06:01,730 --> 01:06:03,710
- Nothing.
- Sir, I'll say again...

886
01:06:03,865 --> 01:06:05,936
- What's in your pocket?
- Nothing.

887
01:06:07,102 --> 01:06:10,208
I'm gonna ask you again,
what's in your pocket, sir?

888
01:06:11,273 --> 01:06:12,684
All right.

889
01:06:12,841 --> 01:06:15,515
I have, in my pocket...

890
01:06:15,677 --> 01:06:18,385
a couple of "hambwortsforts".

891
01:06:19,047 --> 01:06:20,890
What?

892
01:06:22,150 --> 01:06:25,461
I have in my pocket...

893
01:06:25,787 --> 01:06:28,267
a couple of "dolvargars".

894
01:06:28,957 --> 01:06:30,300
Sir?

895
01:06:31,126 --> 01:06:37,099
- Sir, in your pocket you have...?
- All right, I have four "hanholders".

896
01:06:37,432 --> 01:06:39,139
I'm sorry. Once more.

897
01:06:40,702 --> 01:06:41,976
Again!

898
01:06:42,137 --> 01:06:43,616
- Sir...
- Hey, what's that?

899
01:06:45,874 --> 01:06:48,582
- Sir. Sir, I'm losing my patience.
- Oh, you are?

900
01:06:48,743 --> 01:06:50,313
- You are losing your patience?
- Yes.

901
01:06:50,478 --> 01:06:53,254
I'm simply telling you I have
a couple of "tamburthers".

902
01:06:53,615 --> 01:06:57,028
I've got an End darter down on six.
I've got an End darter down on six!

903
01:06:57,185 --> 01:06:59,893
- Locked and loaded, sir!
- Show me your hands, sir!

904
01:07:00,055 --> 01:07:01,830
All right, I'll just show you.

905
01:07:02,857 --> 01:07:05,269
- No, no, no! Stay here, sir.
- Sic him, W!

906
01:07:19,474 --> 01:07:23,251
- Yes, that's him!
- Inspector, what is a "damburgert"?

907
01:07:23,411 --> 01:07:26,881
Inspector, how does it feel
to have let down the nation?

908
01:07:32,520 --> 01:07:37,026
So much for the heroic
Inspector Clouseau.

909
01:07:39,127 --> 01:07:43,667
Well, this is a glorious day
for France.

910
01:07:44,232 --> 01:07:46,007
How so, chief inspector?

911
01:07:46,167 --> 01:07:48,977
Because a stupid idiot
named Clouseau...

912
01:07:49,137 --> 01:07:53,244
is going to be stripped of his rank
while I take over his case.

913
01:07:53,408 --> 01:07:55,649
You have a second man
named Clouseau?

914
01:07:55,810 --> 01:07:59,189
My God. Leave us alone
for a moment.

915
01:07:59,347 --> 01:08:02,920
You, out. Go, go. Go.
I must have a private word...

916
01:08:03,084 --> 01:08:06,031
with Inspector Clouseau.

917
01:08:06,187 --> 01:08:07,791
Understand something, Clouseau.

918
01:08:07,956 --> 01:08:11,426
When I made you an inspector,
it was not because I thought...

919
01:08:11,593 --> 01:08:13,698
you had any value as a detective.

920
01:08:13,862 --> 01:08:19,175
It was because I thought you were the
stupidest policeman in all of France.

921
01:08:19,567 --> 01:08:22,844
A hopeless, deluded idiot.

922
01:08:23,271 --> 01:08:25,649
Then I was not promoted
for my merits?

923
01:08:25,840 --> 01:08:29,344
I only made you inspector
because I needed someone...

924
01:08:29,511 --> 01:08:32,048
who would quietly get
nowhere until I was ready...

925
01:08:32,213 --> 01:08:34,215
to take over the case myself.

926
01:08:34,682 --> 01:08:36,662
I was trying to catch a killer.

927
01:08:36,818 --> 01:08:39,355
You were trying...

928
01:08:40,989 --> 01:08:45,836
You were trying to become a hero.
Well, you will be stripped...

929
01:08:45,994 --> 01:08:48,565
of your rank,
ridiculed by the media...

930
01:08:48,730 --> 01:08:50,334
and I will be done with you.

931
01:08:50,498 --> 01:08:54,674
And now if you will excuse me,
ex-inspector, I must go and prepare...

932
01:08:54,836 --> 01:08:58,374
for the arrest which will win me
the Medal of Honor...

933
01:08:58,540 --> 01:09:03,614
catapult me to the National
Assembly, and after that, who knows?

934
01:09:04,245 --> 01:09:07,351
- Goodbye, Clouseau.
- Shall we lock him up?

935
01:09:07,515 --> 01:09:09,051
Look at him.

936
01:09:09,217 --> 01:09:13,324
He is finished.
Let him go home to obscurity.

937
01:09:22,797 --> 01:09:24,401
You knew?

938
01:09:47,288 --> 01:09:48,995
Ponton...

939
01:09:49,491 --> 01:09:51,767
things were not
as I supposed they were.

940
01:09:53,061 --> 01:09:56,702
And if I ever made
you look foolish...

941
01:09:57,265 --> 01:09:59,472
I am sorry.

942
01:10:00,702 --> 01:10:04,411
It was an honor
serving under you, sir.

943
01:10:16,417 --> 01:10:18,192
Good one.

944
01:10:41,976 --> 01:10:43,853
The Internet.

945
01:10:44,012 --> 01:10:45,821
Hello, old friend.

946
01:10:48,583 --> 01:10:52,156
To download your new
cell-phone ringtone...

947
01:10:52,587 --> 01:10:56,501
press the button
that says download.

948
01:10:57,091 --> 01:11:01,938
I take the mouse and I click,
but do not drag...

949
01:11:02,096 --> 01:11:06,044
the button that says download.

950
01:11:16,544 --> 01:11:19,150
Gentlemen, and lady,
good morning.

951
01:11:19,314 --> 01:11:22,386
Meet Dr. Li How Pang.

952
01:11:22,550 --> 01:11:25,793
He was, of course, in the VIP box
when Gluant was killed.

953
01:11:25,954 --> 01:11:29,834
Coincidentally, Dr. Pang would
send Gluant large sums of money.

954
01:11:29,991 --> 01:11:34,371
Presumably, Gluant was to invest
these sums on Pang's behalf.

955
01:11:34,529 --> 01:11:38,477
But being a compulsive gambler,
Gluant took the money...

956
01:11:38,633 --> 01:11:40,977
and gambled it all away.

957
01:11:41,569 --> 01:11:43,981
So Pang had the motive.

958
01:11:44,372 --> 01:11:47,148
He had the opportunity.

959
01:11:47,308 --> 01:11:51,950
Pang is in France
for the president's ball tonight.

960
01:11:52,113 --> 01:11:55,959
We will arrest him there
for the murder of Yves Gluant.

961
01:11:56,117 --> 01:11:58,222
Bravo, chief inspector.

962
01:11:59,053 --> 01:12:02,057
I am pleased to announce that
I am personally taking over...

963
01:12:02,223 --> 01:12:06,433
the Pink Panther investigation
and that an arrest is imminent.

964
01:12:06,594 --> 01:12:08,369
- Thank you.
- Chief inspector...

965
01:12:08,529 --> 01:12:10,839
the coroner has announced
that Bizu was killed...

966
01:12:10,999 --> 01:12:14,378
with a perfect shot to the
occipital lobe. Any comments?

967
01:12:14,535 --> 01:12:16,947
The occipital lobe?

968
01:12:17,872 --> 01:12:19,852
It's irrelevant.

969
01:12:22,710 --> 01:12:25,156
The occipital lobe.

970
01:12:39,227 --> 01:12:41,400
That makes me feel good.

971
01:12:49,170 --> 01:12:51,047
Zoom.

972
01:12:59,280 --> 01:13:02,124
Of course.

973
01:13:06,921 --> 01:13:09,299
Ponton, I need you
over here immediately.

974
01:13:09,457 --> 01:13:12,267
We are back on the case.

975
01:13:15,630 --> 01:13:19,703
Nicole, I believe Bizu and Gluant
were killed by the same person.

976
01:13:19,867 --> 01:13:22,177
And that the killer
will strike again tonight.

977
01:13:22,336 --> 01:13:24,873
I want you to meet me
at the presidential palace.

978
01:13:25,039 --> 01:13:28,213
And bring my vinyl bag marked
presidential palace.

979
01:13:28,376 --> 01:13:32,688
And hurry! Xania is in grave danger.

980
01:13:34,449 --> 01:13:38,488
Ponton, we must get to the
presidential palace immediately!

981
01:13:38,653 --> 01:13:40,997
- Put your seat belt on.
- I don't need a seat belt.

982
01:13:41,155 --> 01:13:42,759
Let's see what this baby can do!

983
01:13:51,065 --> 01:13:53,807
No. Clouseau should not
be on this list.

984
01:13:53,968 --> 01:13:56,710
He is no longer allowed
at state affairs.

985
01:13:56,871 --> 01:14:00,444
He has been disgraced
and humiliated.

986
01:14:00,608 --> 01:14:03,680
But what about all the reporters
who will want to come in?

987
01:14:03,845 --> 01:14:07,987
When the time is right,
let them pour in.

988
01:14:27,969 --> 01:14:29,846
Clouseau.

989
01:14:31,639 --> 01:14:33,744
I'm sorry, but your name
is not on the list.

990
01:14:33,908 --> 01:14:35,649
Not on the list?

991
01:14:36,778 --> 01:14:39,054
Dreyfus must have made sure
you cannot get in.

992
01:14:45,219 --> 01:14:46,596
Ponton.

993
01:14:52,226 --> 01:14:55,036
- Inspector, here is your bag.
- Good work, Nicole.

994
01:14:55,196 --> 01:14:58,405
- What is that?
- Camouflage. Let's go.

995
01:14:58,566 --> 01:15:00,239
- Nicole.
- Yes?

996
01:15:00,401 --> 01:15:02,677
- One last thing.
- Yes?

997
01:15:08,810 --> 01:15:10,289
It's evening...

998
01:15:10,444 --> 01:15:13,323
and you look beautiful
without your glasses.

999
01:15:42,650 --> 01:15:43,890
- Chief inspector.
- What?

1000
01:15:44,546 --> 01:15:48,517
Our men have reported a sighting
of Inspector Clouseau.

1001
01:15:48,684 --> 01:15:50,095
Clouseau?

1002
01:15:50,786 --> 01:15:55,428
I know what he's up to. He wants
to try to make the arrest himself.

1003
01:15:55,590 --> 01:15:59,834
If you see Clouseau,
put him in cuffs for trespassing...

1004
01:15:59,995 --> 01:16:02,066
and parade him through the party.

1005
01:16:02,230 --> 01:16:05,905
I want all men on alert.
Arrest him outside.

1006
01:16:11,450 --> 01:16:14,363
Dr. Pang has arrived.

1007
01:16:17,056 --> 01:16:20,333
We will take him after the first song.

1008
01:16:21,227 --> 01:16:22,797
Yes, yes. Very true.

1009
01:17:36,068 --> 01:17:38,605
Good work, Ponton. We're in.

1010
01:17:40,272 --> 01:17:42,081
Look!

1011
01:17:42,942 --> 01:17:45,115
It's the killer! After him!

1012
01:17:45,277 --> 01:17:50,283
- Change outfits.
- Stop! Turn around.

1013
01:17:50,449 --> 01:17:51,757
Who are you?

1014
01:17:51,917 --> 01:17:56,957
- What are you doing here?
- We are, we are two, we are...

1015
01:17:57,122 --> 01:17:59,193
- I'll tell you exactly who we are.
- Yes.

1016
01:17:59,358 --> 01:18:01,599
- We are...
- I've been looking for you everywhere.

1017
01:18:01,760 --> 01:18:03,603
Where the hell have you been?

1018
01:18:03,762 --> 01:18:06,265
- You know these two?
- Of course I know them.

1019
01:18:06,465 --> 01:18:09,708
They are Xania's backup dancers.
They go on in the third act...

1020
01:18:09,868 --> 01:18:11,939
with the Komodo dragon
and the snow machine.

1021
01:18:12,104 --> 01:18:14,448
Why do you think they are
dressed like that, for fun?

1022
01:18:14,607 --> 01:18:17,144
- Prove it.
- We don't have to prove...

1023
01:18:54,847 --> 01:18:56,724
Can't you see these dancers
are exhausted?

1024
01:18:56,882 --> 01:18:58,259
Go and fetch them some water.

1025
01:19:00,486 --> 01:19:02,466
That was fantastic.

1026
01:19:02,888 --> 01:19:04,561
- You think so?
- You are...

1027
01:19:06,125 --> 01:19:08,696
an amazing woman.

1028
01:19:13,098 --> 01:19:15,840
Inspector, the killer.

1029
01:19:30,049 --> 01:19:33,428
Now I am ready to catch a killer.

1030
01:19:48,967 --> 01:19:50,037
Stop!

1031
01:19:50,469 --> 01:19:52,745
Stop in the name of the law.

1032
01:19:53,472 --> 01:19:54,951
Get him!

1033
01:19:55,474 --> 01:19:57,784
- Bravo!
- Bravo!

1034
01:19:59,912 --> 01:20:03,189
Ponton, you follow him that way.
I'll go this way and cut him off.

1035
01:20:06,185 --> 01:20:07,425
Stop!

1036
01:20:09,488 --> 01:20:11,126
Turn around.

1037
01:20:12,124 --> 01:20:14,934
- You're under arre...
- You are under arrest!

1038
01:20:15,094 --> 01:20:17,074
Ponton! After him!

1039
01:20:17,396 --> 01:20:18,807
Now.

1040
01:20:19,665 --> 01:20:20,735
Go, go!

1041
01:20:21,100 --> 01:20:24,604
Well, Dr. Pang.
In the name of the statutes...

1042
01:20:25,003 --> 01:20:27,483
and laws of the great nation
of France...

1043
01:20:29,108 --> 01:20:32,817
I arrest you for the murder
of Yves Gluant.

1044
01:20:37,583 --> 01:20:39,460
Clouseau! Arrest him.

1045
01:20:41,153 --> 01:20:42,791
Which one is he?

1046
01:20:42,955 --> 01:20:44,229
That would be him.

1047
01:20:48,594 --> 01:20:52,474
In the name of the statutes and laws
of the great nation of France...

1048
01:20:52,631 --> 01:20:54,907
I arrest you for the murder
of Yves Gluant.

1049
01:20:55,067 --> 01:20:57,445
Yuri, the trainer who trains.

1050
01:20:59,772 --> 01:21:01,479
And who are you?

1051
01:21:01,640 --> 01:21:04,484
I am Inspector Jacques Clouseau.

1052
01:21:05,344 --> 01:21:07,517
Gluant was nothing!

1053
01:21:07,679 --> 01:21:09,283
I drew up the plays.

1054
01:21:09,815 --> 01:21:13,353
He takes credit for brilliant
French defense which I gave him...

1055
01:21:13,519 --> 01:21:17,661
and treats me like I'm dead. Fine.
Now he is dead from Chinese poison.

1056
01:21:19,024 --> 01:21:21,971
Inspector, what made you
think it was him?

1057
01:21:22,127 --> 01:21:27,338
But, Ponton, think back.
You were there.

1058
01:21:28,934 --> 01:21:30,004
Why do you bother me?

1059
01:21:30,169 --> 01:21:31,807
Why did you bring me here?
I'm busy.

1060
01:21:33,005 --> 01:21:35,007
The coach was killed
with Chinese poison.

1061
01:21:35,174 --> 01:21:36,778
You should look
for soccer trainers.

1062
01:21:38,443 --> 01:21:42,016
They are required to have a
knowledge of Chinese herbs.

1063
01:21:42,681 --> 01:21:44,285
She was right, of course.

1064
01:21:44,716 --> 01:21:48,596
According to statute 87223, every
trainer of the national soccer team...

1065
01:21:48,754 --> 01:21:50,825
must have a knowledge
of Chinese herbs.

1066
01:21:51,156 --> 01:21:54,865
This made it easy for him
to murder Gluant.

1067
01:21:55,828 --> 01:21:58,331
- And Bizu?
- Simple.

1068
01:21:58,497 --> 01:22:01,944
Bizu had often heard
Yuri's rants against Gluant.

1069
01:22:02,100 --> 01:22:05,547
So Bizu blackmailed Yuri
and got himself killed.

1070
01:22:06,371 --> 01:22:08,749
Oh, it's you.

1071
01:22:11,510 --> 01:22:13,387
A stunning shot to the head...

1072
01:22:13,879 --> 01:22:16,758
burrowing deeply
into the occipital lobe.

1073
01:22:16,915 --> 01:22:18,622
But Yuri is a soccer trainer.

1074
01:22:18,784 --> 01:22:21,321
That shot was made
by an expert marksman.

1075
01:22:21,486 --> 01:22:23,432
Chief inspector, I'm sure
you're familiar...

1076
01:22:23,589 --> 01:22:25,432
with Russian army statute 611.

1077
01:22:26,091 --> 01:22:27,365
Well, of course.

1078
01:22:27,526 --> 01:22:29,665
All members must be...

1079
01:22:29,828 --> 01:22:31,865
- expert marksmen...
- expert marksmen...

1080
01:22:32,030 --> 01:22:35,603
and understand the location
of the occipital...

1081
01:22:35,767 --> 01:22:37,940
- Occipital lobe, of course.
- Yes.

1082
01:22:38,103 --> 01:22:41,084
- Very true.
- Yes, Yuri.

1083
01:22:41,240 --> 01:22:43,413
Xania is still alive.

1084
01:22:43,575 --> 01:22:47,523
But you hated her. And that's
why you are trying to kill her.

1085
01:22:47,679 --> 01:22:50,558
You hated her because she
went with Bizu and then Gluant...

1086
01:22:50,716 --> 01:22:52,787
and treated you
like you were nothing.

1087
01:22:53,185 --> 01:22:56,997
But you forgot a fundamental truth
about women.

1088
01:22:57,155 --> 01:22:59,601
A woman is like a...

1089
01:22:59,758 --> 01:23:01,738
is like a...

1090
01:23:01,894 --> 01:23:03,271
artichoke.

1091
01:23:04,429 --> 01:23:08,241
You have to do a bit of work
before you get to her heart.

1092
01:23:10,102 --> 01:23:13,083
What about the diamond?
What about the Pink Panther?

1093
01:23:13,238 --> 01:23:18,051
Yes, thank you, Inspector Clouseau
for carrying out my orders.

1094
01:23:18,210 --> 01:23:19,780
Hand over the diamond, Yuri.

1095
01:23:19,945 --> 01:23:22,152
What do I care about
your stinking diamond?

1096
01:23:22,581 --> 01:23:23,992
He does not have the diamond.

1097
01:23:24,149 --> 01:23:26,686
The murderer does not have
the diamond?

1098
01:23:26,852 --> 01:23:29,230
- No.
- Well, then, where is it...

1099
01:23:29,388 --> 01:23:30,992
Inspector Clouseau?

1100
01:23:31,156 --> 01:23:34,103
It is there! In her purse.

1101
01:23:35,460 --> 01:23:36,871
Let me see.

1102
01:23:49,007 --> 01:23:51,749
Sorry, Clouseau, no diamond.

1103
01:24:00,052 --> 01:24:02,225
The purse, please.

1104
01:24:08,093 --> 01:24:09,766
Could you hold that, please?

1105
01:24:21,273 --> 01:24:24,846
After Gluant came to me, he said
he decided to stop cheating on me.

1106
01:24:25,777 --> 01:24:27,950
Then he asked me to marry him...

1107
01:24:30,082 --> 01:24:32,426
and put the ring in my hands.

1108
01:24:34,853 --> 01:24:36,799
After he was killed, I thought...

1109
01:24:36,955 --> 01:24:39,902
if I came forward with the ring,
everyone would think I did it.

1110
01:24:40,058 --> 01:24:42,595
If Gluant gave you the ring
before he died...

1111
01:24:42,761 --> 01:24:48,905
then according to civil statute
812-914B, you are the rightful owner.

1112
01:24:49,067 --> 01:24:51,673
You may keep the Pink Panther.

1113
01:24:57,075 --> 01:24:59,487
But, inspector,
how did you know she had it?

1114
01:24:59,644 --> 01:25:01,146
It was simple, Ponton.

1115
01:25:01,313 --> 01:25:04,522
I was looking at a photo of myself
at the checkpoint.

1116
01:25:04,683 --> 01:25:06,492
Something caught my eye.

1117
01:25:06,651 --> 01:25:09,894
Xania's purse passing through
the x-ray machine.

1118
01:25:10,389 --> 01:25:12,892
I enlarged the photo...

1119
01:25:13,058 --> 01:25:14,537
and in it...

1120
01:25:15,560 --> 01:25:16,834
the Pink Panther.

1121
01:25:16,995 --> 01:25:20,704
- The case is closed!
- Bravo, Clouseau.

1122
01:25:26,438 --> 01:25:28,247
Bravo!

1123
01:25:29,808 --> 01:25:33,119
Clouseau! Clouseau!
Clouseau! Clouseau!

1124
01:25:37,416 --> 01:25:39,488
I can't thank you enough
for giving me...

1125
01:25:39,651 --> 01:25:42,097
the opportunity to solve
the Pink Panther murder.

1126
01:25:42,254 --> 01:25:44,359
Without your decision to put me
on the case...

1127
01:25:44,523 --> 01:25:47,697
who knows, someone else might've
won the Medal of Honor this year.

1128
01:25:47,859 --> 01:25:49,133
Yes, I know.

1129
01:25:49,294 --> 01:25:53,572
I owe it all to you, chief inspector.
Without you, I would be nothing.

1130
01:25:53,732 --> 01:25:57,578
- Perhaps you still are.
- Excellent verbal joust, inspector.

1131
01:25:57,736 --> 01:25:59,943
You idiot! Oh, no.

1132
01:26:00,105 --> 01:26:02,745
- Hit it, Ponton.
- No! Clouseau!

1133
01:26:02,908 --> 01:26:04,546
Stop the car. Dear...

1134
01:26:04,709 --> 01:26:06,347
What?

1135
01:26:06,511 --> 01:26:08,081
Nothing.

1136
01:26:08,580 --> 01:26:09,786
You didn't say...

1137
01:26:09,948 --> 01:26:14,454
Stop the car. Dear God,
I beg of you, stop the car?

1138
01:26:14,619 --> 01:26:16,189
No.

1139
01:26:24,863 --> 01:26:26,809
Does it hurt?

1140
01:26:32,237 --> 01:26:33,614
What?

1141
01:26:35,140 --> 01:26:36,847
I can't understand you.

1142
01:26:41,379 --> 01:26:43,859
You know what,
I think he wants to recline.

1143
01:26:44,015 --> 01:26:45,926
There's a lever right here.

1144
01:26:46,084 --> 01:26:48,189
Oh, it's on the other side, I'm sorry.

1145
01:26:48,353 --> 01:26:51,197
A bit of a reach.
Wait a minute. I'll get it.

1146
01:26:51,356 --> 01:26:53,302
I'll get it right here.

1147
01:26:53,558 --> 01:26:56,471
Is right back here.

1148
01:26:59,131 --> 01:27:00,940
There must be a simpler way...

1149
01:27:01,099 --> 01:27:04,103
of working this...
Oh, there's a remote control...

1150
01:27:04,269 --> 01:27:05,373
so that you can just...

1151
01:27:05,537 --> 01:27:08,416
It's sensitive! I hardly touched it!
But it goes up...

1152
01:27:12,811 --> 01:27:14,449
That's it! That's it!

1153
01:27:18,583 --> 01:27:22,156
- You know, Ponton.
- Yes, inspector.

1154
01:27:22,988 --> 01:27:25,935
This is a very hard time
for Inspector Dreyfus.

1155
01:27:26,091 --> 01:27:29,470
It is important that
we show compassion.

1156
01:27:29,628 --> 01:27:32,871
And we must use the gentle
healing power of laughter.

1157
01:27:55,020 --> 01:27:56,829
This is going to hurt.

1158
01:27:59,224 --> 01:28:02,000
Clouseau!

1159
01:28:05,630 --> 01:28:07,974
That breeze feels good.
